The paper discusses reinforcement learning with deep neural networks and the vulnerability of these networks to adversarial attacks. This topic falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential security threats for safety-critical systems such as drones and self-driving cars, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of deep neural networks in image recognition and analysis is also mentioned, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact on autonomous systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
